cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY

The paper proposes a framework for the emergence of general intelligence through the evolution of agents and their neural networks. The chosen control mechanism is based on spiking neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses self-supervised learning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework involves the evolution of network topologies, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the ability of agents to adapt to mutable environments, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
